# subdoc = 3.5
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = This is also why the Dorians claim both Tragedy and Comedy as their own—Comedy is claimed by the Megarians (both those here, on the grounds that it arose during their democracy, and those in Sicily, for the poet Epicharmus was from there, living much earlier than Chionides and Magnes), and Tragedy is claimed by some of those in the Peloponnese—using these names as evidence.
# literal_translation = Wherefore also they-claim-for-themselves of-the both tragedy and of-the comedy the Dorians, of-the indeed comedy the Megarians, both those here as on the with them democracy having-arisen, and those from Sicily (from-there for was Epicharmus the poet, by-much earlier being of-Chionides and of-Magnes), and of-the tragedy some of-those in Peloponnese, making the names a-sign.
