# sentence_id = 83
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Tragedy, then, is an imitation of an action that is serious and complete, and which has magnitude, in language embellished with each kind of artistic ornament, the several kinds being found in separate parts of the play; [presented] by actors and not through narrative; through pity and fear effecting the purgation of such emotions.
