# sentence_id = 146
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = For in composing the Odyssey, he did not include everything that happened to the hero—for example, his being wounded on Parnassus or his feigning madness during the recruitment—since the occurrence of one of these did not make the occurrence of the other necessary or probable; instead, he constructed the Odyssey around a single action of the kind we describe, and similarly also the Iliad.
# literal_translation = For making the Odyssey, he did not make all as many things as happened to him, such as on the one hand to have been wounded in the Parnassus, on the other hand to have pretended to be mad in the recruitment, of which things the one having happened it was nothing necessary or likely for the other to happen, but around one action, such as we say, he constructed the Odyssey, and similarly also the Iliad.
