# sentence_id = 147
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Therefore, just as in the other mimetic arts a single representation is of a single object, so too the plot, since it is a representation of an action, must be of a single and whole action, and the parts of the events must be so constructed that if any part is displaced or removed, the whole is disturbed and moved.
# literal_translation = It is necessary then, just as even in the other mimetic [arts] the one representation is of one [object], thus also the plot, since of an action representation it is, to be of one and of this whole, and the parts to have been constructed of the events thus so as with some part being transposed or being removed the whole to be disturbed and to be moved.
