# sentence_id = 198
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = The prologue is the entire part of a tragedy before the parodos of the chorus; an episode is the entire part of a tragedy between whole choral songs; the exode is the entire part of a tragedy after which there is no choral song. Of the choral part, the parodos is the first speech of the whole chorus; a stasimon is a choral song without anapests or trochees; a kommos is a joint lament of the chorus and the actors.
# literal_translation = Is but prologue indeed part whole of-tragedy the before of-chorus of-parodos, episode but part whole of-tragedy the between of-whole choral of-songs, exode but part whole of-tragedy after which not is of-chorus song, of-choral but parodos indeed the first speech of-whole chorus, stasimon but song of-chorus the without anapest and trochee, kommos but lament common of-chorus and from stage.
