# sentence_id = 210
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = For whereas in earlier times poets used to run through whatever myths came along, now the finest tragedies are composed around a few families—for instance, about Alcmaeon and Oedipus and Orestes and Meleager and Thyestes and Telephus, and all others to whom it has happened either to suffer or to do terrible things.
# literal_translation = Before the indeed for the poets the random myths were-counting-out, now but around few families the finest tragedies are-composed, such-as about Alcmaeon and Oedipus and Orestes and Meleager and Thyestes and Telephus, and to-as-many-as others it-has-happened either to-suffer terrible-things or to-do.
