# sentence_id = 370
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 20.3
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = A vowel is that which has an audible sound without impact, such as A and Ω; a semi-vowel is that which has an audible sound with impact, such as Σ and Ρ; a mute is that which has no sound by itself with impact, but becomes audible when combined with those that have some sound, such as Γ and Δ.
# literal_translation = And it is a vowel indeed having an audible sound without impact, such as the A and the Ω, and a semi-vowel [is] that having an audible sound with impact, such as the Σ and the Ρ, and a mute [is] that with impact by itself indeed having no sound, but with the [things] having some sound becoming audible, such as the Γ and the Δ.
