# subdoc = 21.21
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Among the nouns themselves, some are masculine, some are feminine, and some are intermediate. Masculine are all those that end in N, R, and the double letters formed from these (which are two, Psi and Xi); feminine are all those formed from vowels that end in the naturally long ones, such as Eta and Omega, and among the lengthened ones, those ending in Alpha.
# literal_translation = Of the themselves but nouns the indeed masculine the but feminine the but between, masculine indeed as-many end into the N and R, and as-many from this (these but are two, Psi and Xi), feminine but as-many from the vowels both into the always long, such as into Eta and Omega, and of the being-lengthened into Alpha.
