# prose_translation = And it would be the same if one should substitute common words and say, instead of the poetic originals, "but now since I am small, weak and unseemly," and instead of "having set down an unseemly stool and a tiny table," "having set down a wretched stool and a small table," or "the shores cry out" instead of "the shores roar."
# literal_translation = And if someone should speak the common [words] substituting: "now but me being small both and weak and unseemly"; and [for] "a stool unseemly having set down a small both table," "a stool wretched having set down a small both table"; and [for] the "shores roar," "shores cry out."
