# prose_translation = Furthermore, Ariphrades mocked the tragic poets because they used expressions that no one would use in ordinary speech, such as 'domaton apo' instead of 'apo domaton', and 'sethen', and 'ego de nin', and 'Achilleos peri' instead of 'peri Achilleos', and other such things.
# literal_translation = Still but Ariphrades the tragic-poets mocked, because which no-one would say in the dialect, these they-use, such-as the 'houses from' but not 'from houses', and the 'of-thee', and the 'I but him', and the 'Achilles about' but not 'about Achilles', and as-many other such-things.
