# prose_translation = Consequently, while the Iliad and the Odyssey each provide material for only one or two tragedies, the Cypria provides many, and the Little Iliad more than eight—for example, the Judgment of Arms, Philoctetes, Neoptolemus, Eurypylus, the Begging Expedition, the Laconian Women, the Sack of Ilium, the Sailing Away, Sinon, and the Trojan Women.
# literal_translation = Therefore out-of on-the-one-hand Iliad and Odyssey one tragedy is-made of-each or two only, out-of but Cypria many, and out-of the little Iliad more eight, such-as of-arms judgment, Philoctetes, Neoptolemus, Eurypylus, beggary, Laconian-women, of-Ilium sack and sailing-away and Sinon and Trojan-women.
