# prose_translation = Regarding whether something has been said or done well or not, one must not only look at whether the deed or word itself is virtuous or base, but also at the person acting or speaking, to whom, or when, or for whom, or for what purpose—for example, so that a greater good might come to be or a greater evil might be averted.
