# prose_translation = Other cases are explained by the custom of language, as when people speak of "mixed wine"; hence the phrase "greave of newly-wrought tin" has been made, and people call those who work iron "braziers," whence Ganymede is said to "pour wine" for Zeus, although the gods do not drink wine; this too might be explained as a metaphor.
